<section xml:id="sec-basic-operations" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Related to basic operations</title>

  <p> We denote by <m>0_n</m> the <m>n\times n</m> matrix with all its entries zero. We call <m>0_n</m> the zero matrix. We denote by <m>I_n</m> the <m>n\times n</m> matrix with all its diagonal entries <m>1</m>, and all other non-diagonal entries zero. We call <m>I_n</m> the identity matrix.</p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
          Show that for any matrix <m>A\in M_{n\times n}(\mathbb{R})</m> the following is true. <me>A+0_n=0_n+A=A\quad\text{and}\quad A\, I_n=I_n\, A=A</me>
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          Let <m>A=\left(\begin{smallmatrix}1\amp 3\\0\amp 4\end{smallmatrix}\right)\in M_{2\times 2}(\mathbb{R})</m>. Find <m>B\in M_{2\times 2}(\mathbb{R})</m> such that <m>A+B=\left(\begin{smallmatrix}1\amp 0\\1\amp 0\end{smallmatrix}\right).</m> 
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>  


</section>